The best interval we can use (the interval whose points are given that's closest to $x=-4$) is the interval between $x=-6$ and $x=-3$. Let's find the average rate of change between those points.

$\begin{align}
h'(-4)&\approx\dfrac{h(-3)-h(-6)}{-3-(-6)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-20-(-36)}{3}
\\\\
&\approx5.33
\end{align}$
